== Role of Charles' Spanish partisans. ==

I'm concerned because the role played by the Spanish followers of Archduke Charles in the siege is nearly ignored. Two contemporaneous writers, Narcís Feliu de la Penya and Francesc de Castellví i Obando, recorded that the troops which did most to repel the Bourbonic assault were not English, but the Spanish companies of Francisco de Sandoval (in fact, Prince George's bodyguard company) and Jaume Burguy (of Catalan miquelets) [http://books.google.es/books?ei=RKR_UcnpEMir7Ab1tYDgCg&hl=es&id=lXhUAAAAYAAJ&dq=annales+de+catalu%C3%B1a&jtp=526#v=onepage&q&f=false 1] [http://books.google.es/books?ei=0aZ_Ueu8L-fm7AaI4IDIDQ&hl=es&id=H2xpAAAAMAAJ&dq=francisco+sandoval+gibraltar&q=francisco+sandoval#search_anchor 2]. --[[User:Weymar Horren|Weymar Horren]] ([[User talk:Weymar Horren|talk]]) 11:21, 30 April 2013 (UTC)

